Nau"}], "venue": "Lancet (London, England)", "year": 1994, "keywords": ["legal approach", "professional patient relationship"], "page_start": "785", "page_end": "785", "lang": "en", "volume": "343", "issue": "8900", "issn": "0140-6736", "doi": "10.1016/S0140-6736(94)91852-X", "url": ["http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/S0140-6736(94)91852-X", "http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/11644596?report=xml&format=text"]}
{"id": "53e99837b7602d970205e5dc", "title": "Network information flow", "authors": [{"name": "Rudolf Ahlswede"}, {"name": "Ning Cai"}, {"name": "Shuo-yen Robert Li"}, {"name": "Raymond W. Yeung"}], "venue": "IEEE Transactions on Information Theory", "year": 2000, "keywords": ["network coding", "index terms\u2014diversity coding", "multicast", "multiterminal source coding.", "switching", "encoding", "information flow", "point to point", "indexing terms", "spine", "application software", "communication networks", "directed graphs", "switches", "max flow min cut theorem", "source coding", "bandwidth", "computer network", "directed graph", "computer networks", "multicasting"], "n_citation": 7484, "page_start": "1204", "page_end": "1216", "lang": "en", "volume": "46", "issue": "4", "doi": "10.1109/18.850663", "url": ["http://dx.doi.org/10.1109/18.850663"], "abstract": "We introduce a new class of problems called network information flow which is inspired by computer network applica- tions. Consider a point-to-point communication network on which a number of information sources are to be mulitcast to certain sets of destinations. We assume that the information sources are mu- tually independent. The problem is to characterize the admissible coding rate region. This model subsumes all previously studied models along the same line. In this paper, we study the problem with one information source, and we have obtained a simple char- acterization of the admissible coding rate region. Our result can be regarded as the Max-flow Min-cut Theorem for network informa- tion flow. Contrary to one's intuition, our work reveals that it is in general not optimal to regard the information to be multicast as a \"fluid\" which can simply be routed or replicated. Rather, by em- ploying coding at the nodes, which we refer to as network coding, bandwidth can in general be saved. This finding may have signifi- cant impact on future design of switching systems.", "references": ["53e9a64ab7602d9702f791d8", "53e9b42fb7602d9703f2685a", "53e9985fb7602d9702098a11", "53e9ab73b7602d970351496d", "56d833a3dabfae2eee320bb5", "53e9af1fb7602d970395ccdb", "53e9ab73b7602d970351496c", "53e9af39b7602d97039743c0", "53e99a1fb7602d9702273ffc", "53e9a9b7b7602d970331368c", "53e9aefcb7602d9703930e5e", "53e9af39b7602d97039735bc", "53e99b16b7602d97023a78f8", "53e9a098b7602d9702980688", "53e9983db7602d9702067c7a", "53e9b911b7602d97044f73ab"]}

Broese van Groenou", "org": "Philips Forschungslaboratorium Eindhoven Netherlands Eindhoven Netherlands"}, {"name": "Philips Forschungslaboratorium"}], "venue": "Applied Physics A", "year": 1973, "keywords": ["magnetic properties", "time constant", "indexation", "electron transfer"], "page_start": "47", "page_end": "58", "lang": "en", "volume": "2", "issue": "2", "doi": "10.1007/BF00934173", "url": ["http://dx.doi.org/10.1007/BF00934173"], "abstract": "\n Abstract\u00a0\u00a0In ferrites a large number of after-effects are found, with time constants between nano-seconds and years. In this review\n the after-effects due to ion-and electron motion will be treated. One finds:\n \n \n 1)\u00a0\n \n single-ion effects in combination with lattice deformations, e.g. Mn3+;\n \n \n \n \n 2)\u00a0\n \n ion effects caused by mobile vacancies, e.g. Co2+;\n \n \n \n \n 3)\u00a0\n \n effects due to electron transfer:\n \n \n \n \n a)\u00a0\n \n Co2+\u2212Co3+\n \n \n \n \n \n b)\u00a0\n \n Me2+\u2212Fe3+, in combination with Me4+ and vacancies.\n \n \n \n \n c)\u00a0\n \n Me4+\u2212Fe2+, with Me=Si, Ti (photomagnetic effect).\n \n \n \n \n \n \n The electron transfer is found to be related to electrical effects. In analogy to the photoelectric effect, one has found\n that illumination produces changes in magnetic properties. Generally speaking, one has in ferrites as many problems with donors\n and acceptors as in other semiconductors. Information from magnetic measurements helps to elucidate their nature.\n \n \n \n ", "references": ["53e9ad64b7602d970374cb3f", "53e9bb80b7602d97047c597e", "56d83548dabfae2eee3b9841", "56d8fba6dabfae2eeeb6d72a", "53e99ff5b7602d97028d74dd"]}

{"id": "53e99837b7602d970205e604", "title": "Natural interface exploration", "authors": [{"name": "Marius Brade", "org": "Technische Universit\u00e4t Dresden, Dresden, Germany"}, {"name": "Mandy Keck", "org": "Technische Universit\u00e4t Dresden, Dresden, Germany"}, {"name": "Thomas Gr\u00fcnder", "org": "Technische Universit\u00e4t Dresden, Dresden, Germany"}, {"name": "Mathias M\u00fcller", "org": "Technische Universit\u00e4t Dresden, Dresden, Germany"}, {"name": "Rainer Groh", "org": "Technische Universit\u00e4t Dresden, Dresden, Germany"}], "venue": "Tangible and Embedded Interaction", "year": 2013, "keywords": ["required interaction", "offer closing thought", "own interface mock-up", "natural user", "natural interface exploration studio", "new kind", "natural interface exploration", "studio organizer", "natural substance", "natural user interface", "interaction design", "interface design"], "n_citation": 4, "lang": "en", "doi": "10.1145/2460625.2460720", "url": ["http://dx.doi.org/10.1145/2460625.2460720", "http://doi.acm.org/10.1145/2460625.2460720", "http://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=2460625.2460720&COLL=DL&DL=acm&preflayout=flat"], "abstract": "Finding new and compelling approaches to interaction design for natural user interfaces, is challenging. The Natural Interface Exploration studio will offer participants the opportunity to explore interaction design for natural user interfaces based on physical substances that are used in everyday life. Studio organizers will present an overview of their methodology, providing examples of their experience [1, 2] and comparing it to other approaches. They will demonstrate how they analyze natural substances regarding the aspects of visualization and interaction and what kind of interfaces resulted [3, 4, 5] from these findings in initial workshops (see Figure 3 and 4). Following the demonstration, participants will form teams and collaboratively decide which substances or materials they would like to analyze. After examining and charting relevant aspects, the teams will chose a certain task to be solved with a new kind of interface. Example tasks will be provided by the studio organizers. The next step will be to decompose the tasks into required interaction and information needs. Finally participants will develop their own interface mock-up using stop motion or paper prototyping. Finally, studio organizers will facilitate a group critique session and offer closing thoughts on employing this methodology in one's creative TEI practice.", "references": ["53e99fe4b7602d97028c206d", "53e9aa8eb7602d9703405787", "56d89520dabfae2eee086f8a", "53e9b37bb7602d9703e5c020", "53e9a090b7602d9702975877", "53e9b8dab7602d97044bbd5b", "55323bdc45cec66b6f9dabfc"]}

{"id": "53e99837b7602d970205e606", "title": "Nitrides in Europe", "authors": [{"name": "Alan Mills"}], "venue": "III-Vs Review", "year": 2004, "page_start": "36", "page_end": "38", "lang": "en", "volume": "17", "issue": "8", "issn": "III-Vs Review", "doi": "10.1016/S0961-1290(04)00792-6", "url": ["http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/S0961-1290(04)00792-6"], "abstract": "Although not often reported as such, R&D, equipment and materials supply for III-nitride materials and processes (and related wide bandgap materials) are widespread in Europe. In the first of a two part series, Dr Alan Mills reports on research that has been on going for many years, supported by a significant number of universities and companies. Countries including France, Germany, Poland, Sweden, Switzerland, Belgium and the UK have multiple programmes for academic research plus companies that are developing or offering state-of-the-art commercial products. Even smaller states such as Latvia have active nitride programmes supported by international fund agencies eg, NATO and the EU. Nitride laser diodes have been developed at German universities and more recently the University of Sheffield reports on development of its first nitride laser, in conjunction with Chinese researchers."}

{"id": "53e99837b7602d970205e60a", "title": "Neurotransmitters in epilepsy", "authors": [{"name": "G.H. Fromm", "org": "Department of Neurology, University of Pittsburgh, Pittsburgh, PA, USA"}], "venue": "Electroencephalography and Clinical Neurophysiology", "year": 1993, "page_start": "259", "page_end": "259", "lang": "en", "volume": "87", "issue": "4", "issn": "Electroencephalography and Clinical Neurophysiology", "doi": "10.1016/0013-4694(93)90032-Q", "url": ["http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/0013-4694(93)90032-Q"]}
{"id": "53e99837b7602d970205e60b", "title": "Noradrenaline-induced emesis", "authors": [{"name": "D.B. Beleslin", "org": "Department of Pharmacology, Medical Faculty, P.O. Box 662, 11000 Beograd, Yugoslavia"}, {"name": "M. \u0160trbac", "org": "Department of Pharmacology, Medical Faculty, P.O. Box 662, 11000 Beograd, Yugoslavia"}], "venue": "Neuropharmacology", "year": 1987, "keywords": ["emetic region of the brainstem reticular formation", "alpha-2 postsynaptic adrenoceptors", "noradrenaline", "emesis", "area postrema"], "page_start": "1157", "page_end": "1165", "lang": "en", "volume": "26", "issue": "8", "issn": "Neuropharmacology", "doi": "10.1016/0028-3908(87)90262-0", "url": ["http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/0028-3908(87)90262-0"], "abstract": "The emetic action of noradrenaline was investigated in unanaesthetized cats, after it was injected into the cerebral ventricles through chronically implanted cannulae. Intracerebroventricular injection of noradrenaline produced dose-dependent and shortlasting emesis, which was abolished after ablation of the area postrema. However, copper sulphate, given orally, evoked emesis in cats with an ablated area postrema. The selective alpha-2 adrenoceptor antagonist, yohimbine, as well as the mixed alpha-1 and alpha-2 adrenoceptor blocking drugs, phentolamine, tolazoline, phenoxybenzamine and dihydroergotamine, but not the selective alpha-1 adrenoceptor antagonist, prazosin, all injected into the cerebral ventricles, attenuated or blocked the emesis evoked by intracerebroventricular injection of noradrenaline. Of the alpha-adrenoceptor antagonist, only yohimbine produced dose-dependent inhibition of the emesis induced by noradrenaline. On the contrary, selected beta-adrenoceptor blocking agents, an antimuscarinic drug, a ganglionic blocking agent, an antihistamine, dopamine antagonists and a 5-hydroxytryptamine antagonist, all injected into the cerebral ventricles, had no significant effect on the emesis induced by noradrenaline, similarly injected. The emetic response to intracerebroventricular injection of noradrenaline, as well as to intragastric adminsitration of copper sulphate was not altered in cats pretreated with intracerebroventricular injections of alpha-methyl- p -tyrosine and bretylium. On the other hand, the emetic response to intracerebrocentricular injection of noradrenaline and to intragastric administration of copper sulphate was attentuated or blocked in cats pretreated with reserpine intracerebroventricularly. Moreover, in cats pretreated with intracerebroventricular injection of 6-hydroxydopamine and hemicholinium, the emesis induced by intracerebroventricular administration of noradrenaline but not that produced by intragastric injection of copper sulphate, was depressed. Finally, in cats pretreated with an intracerebroventricular injection of 5,6-dihydroxytryptamine, the emetic response to intracerebroventricular injection of noradrenaline as well as to intragastric administration of copper sulphate was not changed. It is postulated that the emesis produced by noradrenaline, injected into the cerebral ventricles, is mediated through alpha-2 adrenoceptors. These alpha-2 adrenoceptors appear to be located postsynaptically in the area postrema and they transmit emetic impulses from the area postrema to the emetic region of the brainstem reticular formation. The results obtained with reserpine and copper sulphate indicate that monoamines are involved in the regulation of vomiting in the emetic region of the brainstem reticular formation.", "references": ["53e9afccb7602d9703a1bc80", "53e9aa5cb7602d97033cee96", "53e9aa61b7602d97033d30a0", "53e9b88bb7602d970445fe3e", "53e9b6bfb7602d9704244acf", "53e9b823b7602d97043dc891", "53e9bdc6b7602d9704a76aeb", "53e9bb59b7602d9704795a52", "53e9bcbab7602d970493c7c4", "53e99d65b7602d970261f3fc", "53e9b7bbb7602d9704365f74"]}

{"id": "53e99837b7602d970205e60d", "title": "Non-invasive electroretinography.", "authors": [{"name": "F. Carpi"}, {"name": "F. Tomei", "org": "A.S.L. 6, Hospital of\u00a0Livorno, Italy"}], "venue": "Biomedicine & pharmacotherapy = Biom\u00e9decine & pharmacoth\u00e9rapie", "year": 2006, "keywords": ["ocular", "electroretinography", "erg", "recording electrode", "electroretinogram", "non-invasive", "retina"], "n_citation": 5, "page_start": "375", "page_end": "379", "lang": "en", "volume": "60", "issue": "8", "issn": "0753-3322", "doi": "10.1016/j.biopha.2006.07.002", "url": ["http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.biopha.2006.07.002", "http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/16935463?report=xml&format=text"], "abstract": "Electroretinographic (ERG) investigations are conventionally performed by using corneal or conjunctival recording electrodes. Both types have to be placed in contact with the eye, resulting invasive and providing discomfort for the patient. This paper presents a simple technique to detect ERG potentials non-invasively. It relies on the use of a conducting liquid between the eye and an external conductor, which actually derives the ocular potential without any ocular contact. These elements are the basic components of a new type of ERG electrode, referred to as Carpi-Tomei (CT) electrode. The paper describes the assembly of prototype samples of the new electrode. Preliminary testing assessed the feasibility of the proposed non-invasive technique."}

{"id": "53e99837b7602d970205e62b", "title": "Neurostimulators in epilepsy.", "authors": [{"name": "Vicenta Salanova", "org": "Indiana University, University Hospital Department of Neurology Room 1711, 550 University Boulevard Indianapolis IN 46202 USA"}, {"name": "Robert Worth"}], "venue": "Current neurology and neuroscience reports", "year": 2007, "keywords": ["randomized trial", "clinical trial"], "n_citation": 3, "page_start": "315", "page_end": "319", "lang": "en", "volume": "7", "issue": "4", "issn": "1528-4042", "doi": "10.1007/s11910-007-0048-9", "url": ["http://dx.doi.org/10.1007/s11910-007-0048-9", "http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17618538?report=xml&format=text"], "abstract": "A review of electrical stimulation in patients with refractory epilepsy, including animal and human data, shows that there is anatomic and physiologic evidence supporting the role of the thalamus in epilepsy. This has led to a multicenter, prospective randomized trial called the Stimulation of the Anterior Nucleus of the Thalamus for Epilepsy (SANTE trial) that is currently being conducted at several centers in the United States. There is also a multicenter clinical trial for patients with refractory partial epilepsy treated with a cranially implanted responsive neurostimulator (RNS) system. Preliminary reports from the RNS system feasibility trial (the NeuroPace trial) suggest that electrographic seizures can be detected before they evolve into clinical seizures, and that electrical stimulation of the epileptogenic zone can then terminate the electrographic seizures. {"id": "53e99837b7602d970205e630", "title": "Neuroprotection in epilepsy.", "authors": [{"name": "Matthew Walker"}], "venue": "Epilepsia", "year": 2007, "keywords": ["receptors", "neuroprotection", "cell death"], "n_citation": 24, "page_start": "66", "page_end": "68", "lang": "en", "volume": "48 Suppl 8", "issue": "s8", "issn": "0013-9580", "doi": "10.1111/j.1528-1167.2007.01354.x", "url": ["http://dx.doi.org/10.1111/j.1528-1167.2007.01354.x", "http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18330004?report=xml&format=text"], "abstract": "Neuroprotection following status epilepticus should encompass not only the prevention of neuronal death, but also preservation of neuronal and network function. This is critical because these aims are not necessarily equivalent; prevention of neuronal loss, for example, does not inevitably prevent epileptogenesis. There are endogenous neuroprotective mechanisms that can serve dichotomous roles (e.g. ERK 1/2 activation can result in either neuroprotection or promote neuronal death). The roles of potential endogenous mechanisms can depend upon the pattern and timing of their activation. The simplest exogenous neuroprotective mechanism is to halt seizure activity. Other approaches consist of early NMDA receptor antagonism or later inhibition of apoptotic pathways. The problem with the latter approach is that calcium accumulation results in the activation of a number of downstream pathways, the importance of which varies from region to region and in a cell-type specific manner. Neuroprotection in epilepsy is not a straightforward concept, and we need to be clear about our eventual objectives (e.g. preventing cognitive decline). There are numerous possible approaches to neuroprotection, and the efficacy of these depends upon their timing, the specific aims and even the method of status epilepticus induction.", "references": ["53e9a018b7602d97028fae1c", "53e9b815b7602d97043c9927", "53e9a5a8b7602d9702ecf93f", "53e9a0b5b7602d970299ff67", "53e9acf6b7602d97036d1d4b", "53e9bda6b7602d9704a544ac", "53e9bc32b7602d97048a352d", "55a4e770612c6b12aafda699", "55a3ac7dc91b587b095ec150", "53e9b08ab7602d9703af6842", "53e9ab9eb7602d9703548129", "53e9b0d8b7602d9703b53560", "53e9ab43b7602d97034d7895", "53e9b290b7602d9703d3875a", "53e9b634b7602d970418ea46", "53e9a3e1b7602d9702cf4e16", "55a509af612c6b12ab01bd54", "53e9b565b7602d970409edeb", "53e9b725b7602d97042bc902", "53e9a2adb7602d9702bb7210", "53e9b0c2b7602d9703b395ca", "55a5e6bb612c6b12ab312da5", "53e99a30b7602d970228f1ef", "53e99b7eb7602d97024242e0", "53e9be28b7602d9704ae603a", "53e9bd18b7602d97049a318e", "53e99eb5b7602d970277eb2c", "53e9bd9eb7602d9704a46ec5", "53e9ae97b7602d97038b8d04", "53e99addb7602d9702363516", "53e9a4b8b7602d9702dd9c04", "53e9bb08b7602d9704744463", "53e9b3efb7602d9703eddb4d"]}

{"id": "53e99837b7602d970205e640", "title": "Narcissism in emotion", "authors": [{"name": "David Pugmire", "org": "Department of Philosophy|University of Southampton"}], "venue": "Phenomenology and The Cognitive Sciences", "year": 2002, "page_start": "313", "page_end": "326", "lang": "en", "volume": "1", "issue": "3", "doi": "10.1023/A:1021364117802", "url": ["http://dx.doi.org/10.1023/A:1021364117802"], "abstract": "Emotion is always someone's. An emotion is also, at least typically, about something and witnesses the value, or lack of value, in it. Some emotions, such as shame and pride, are actually about the self that has them. But self-concern can insinuate itself into every corner of the emotional life. This occurs when the centre of concern in emotion drifts from the ostensible objects of focus (\u201cI was sorry to hear your bad news\u201d) to the emotion itself, to the drama of it, to its feel, to the fact that one is having it. In an unobvious way, the world becomes backdrop, the self the omnipresent protagonist. The apparent ordering, the natural ordering of subject and object in emotion, is inverted. Emotion undergoes a kind of commodification. Yet this is paradoxical. For it isolates the self and subverts the communication and uptake of emotion by others. Narcissism is inimical to the social character of emotion.", "references": ["53e9b5b6b7602d97040ffbd0", "53e99a0eb7602d9702261c55", "53e997bdb7602d9701fa9e6b"]}

{"id": "53e99837b7602d970205e643", "title": "Normen II: Ermessen", "authors": [{"name": "R\u00fcdiger Lautmann"}], "year": 2011, "lang": "en", "doi": "10.1007/978-3-531-93483-9_6", "url": ["http://dx.doi.org/10.1007/978-3-531-93483-9_6"], "abstract": "\n Juristisches Entscheiden gilt gemeinhin als formell programmiert. Unter Berufung auf Legalit\u00e4t heischen Juristen die Legitimit\u00e4t\n ihres Tuns; mit Argumenten des Sachzwangs, des Es-geht-nicht-anders ideologisiert sich eine Praxis als notwendig und richtig\n zugleich. Politische Fragen und soziale Probleme werden \u201averrechtlicht\u2018 (J. Seifert 1971) und damit teilweise gegen Diskussion\n immunisiert. Leisten Rechtsnormen eigentlich all diese Dienste? Hierzu mu\u00df man das juristische Argumentieren (also eine Argumentation,\n die Schl\u00fcsse aus Rechtsnormen wesentlich enth\u00e4lt) darauf durchleuchten, ob seine Konklusionen von den angerufenen Normen gedeckt\n sind. Ergibt die Norm logisch notwendig die behauptete Konklusion, das hei\u00dft, nur dieser und kein anderer Satz folgt aus der Norm, dann darf die Ableitung als programmiert,\n als von den vorgegebenen Normen her gesteuert gelten. Ist die Konklusion indessen nur logisch hinreichend von der Norm gedeckt, l\u00e4\u00dft also die Norm auch andere Konklusionen zu, dann d\u00fcrfte der Entscheider seinen Standpunkt nicht\n als rechtsnotwendig hinstellen; vielmehr ist die Entscheidung im Rahmen der vorhandenen Alternativen rechtsbeliebig und als\n Auswahl eigens zu rechtfertigen. Merkw\u00fcrdigerweise ignorieren juristische Methodenlehren und Ausbildungen weitgehend diese\n Entscheidungssituation; die hier gebr\u00e4uchlichen Schlagworte wie \u201aInteressen- und G\u00fcterabw\u00e4gung\u2018 verh\u00fcllen mehr als sie klarlegen.\n Wir wollen die Situation, in der das Programm dem Entscheider mehrere Alternativen offenl\u00e4\u00dft, \u201aErmessen\u2018 nennen und untersuchen,\n wie der Richter sich hier verh\u00e4lt.\n \n "}

The adaptive approach derives a noise signature from the noise order statistics and utilizes the signature to denoise the data. The novelty of this approach is in presenting a general-purpose denoising in the sense that it does not need to employ any particular assumption on the structure of the noise-free signal, such as data smoothness or sparsity of the coefficients. An advantage of the method is in denoising the corrupted data in any complete basis transformation (orthogonal or non-orthogonal). Experimental results show that the proposed method, called noise invalidation denoising (NIDe), outperforms existing denoising approaches in terms of mean square error (MSE).", "references": ["53e9b29cb7602d9703d44ad1", "53e9b884b7602d9704454a34", "53e9b890b7602d97044630b3", "53e9bac1b7602d97046ee3be", "558aff15e4b0b32fcb3a208c", "53e9a3edb7602d9702d06b34", "53e9b641b7602d970419fd4c", "53e9b67eb7602d97041e9c91", "55323bdc45cec66b6f9dabfc", "53e99f0ab7602d97027d5b2e", "53e9a8c5b7602d9703217851", "53e9b1c9b7602d9703c580c6"]}
{"id": "53e99837b7602d970205e648", "title": "Network intrusion detection", "authors": [{"name": "B. Mukherjee", "org": "California Univ., Davis, CA"}, {"name": "L. T. Heberlein"}, {"name": "K. N. Levitt"}], "venue": "IEEE Network: The Magazine of Global Internetworking", "year": 1994, "keywords": ["heterogeneous computer network", "corresponding system", "computer system", "network-based idss", "prototype idss", "network intrusion detection", "statistical anomaly detection algorithm", "intrusion detection system", "detection mechanism", "intrusion detection", "intrusion detection problem", "computer networks", "open systems"], "n_citation": 1242, "page_start": "26", "page_end": "41", "lang": "en", "volume": "8", "issue": "3", "doi": "10.1109/65.283931", "url": ["http://dx.doi.org/10.1109/65.283931"], "abstract": "Intrusion detection is a new, retrofit approach for providing a sense of security in existing computers and data networks, while allowing them to operate in their current \"open\" mode. The goal of intrusion detection is to identify unauthorized use, misuse, and abuse of computer systems by both system insiders and external penetrators. The intrusion detection problem is becoming a challenging task due to the proliferation of heterogeneous computer networks since the increased connectivity of computer systems gives greater access to outsiders and makes it easier for intruders to avoid identification. Intrusion detection systems (IDSs) are based on the beliefs that an intruder's behavior will be noticeably different from that of a legitimate user and that many unauthorized actions are detectable. Typically, IDSs employ statistical anomaly and rulebased misuse models in order to detect intrusions. A number of prototype IDSs have been developed at several institutions, and some of them have also been deployed on an experimental basis in operational systems. In the present paper, several host-based and network-based IDSs are surveyed, and the characteristics of the corresponding systems are identified. The host-based systems employ the host operating system's audit trails as the main source of input to detect intrusive activity, while most of the network-based IDSs build their detection mechanism on monitored network traffic, and some employ host audit trails as well. An outline of a statistical anomaly detection algorithm employed in a typical IDS is also included", "references": ["53e99a49b7602d97022ac2fe"]}
{"id": "53e99837b7602d970205e64a", "title": "Normalized Information Distance", "authors": [{"name": "Paul M. B. Vit\u00e1nyi", "org": "CWI, Kruislaan 413 SJ Amsterdam 1098 The Netherlands"}, {"name": "Frank J. Balbach", "org": "Univ. Waterloo"}, {"name": "Rudi L. Cilibrasi", "org": "CWI"}, {"name": "Ming Li", "org": "Univ. Waterloo"}], "venue": "European Journal of Social Psychology", "year": 2008, "keywords": ["compression algorithm", "data mining", "world wide web", "machine learning", "machine translation"], "n_citation": 59, "lang": "en", "volume": "abs/0809.2", "doi": "10.1007/978-0-387-84816-7_3", "url": ["http://dx.doi.org/10.1007/978-0-387-84816-7_3", "http://arxiv.org/abs/0809.2553"], "abstract": "The normalized information distance is a universal distance measure for objects of all kinds. It is based on Kolmogorov complexity and thus uncomputable, but there are ways to utilize it. First, compression algorithms can be used to approximate the Kolmogorov complexity if the objects have a string representation. Second, for names and abstract concepts, page count statistics from the World Wide Web can be used. These practical realizations of the normalized information distance can then be applied to machine learning tasks, expecially clustering, to perform feature-free and parameter-free data mining. This chapter discusses the theoretical foundations of the normalized information distance and both practical realizations. It presents numerous examples of successful real-world applications based on these distance measures, ranging from bioinformatics to music clustering to machine translation.", "references": ["53e99a85b7602d97022f8298", "53e9a34ab7602d9702c549ac", "53e9b666b7602d97041cb186", "53e9a1bdb7602d9702ab5fdd", "53e997e9b7602d9701fe3fe1", "53e99addb7602d970236264f", "53e9a3a5b7602d9702cb4d76", "53e9b586b7602d97040c6ca5", "53e9bb93b7602d97047d7af2", "53e99f42b7602d97028147ba", "53e9b550b7602d97040895cb", "53e9984fb7602d970208510e", "53e9bde9b7602d9704a9c14a", "53e99a67b7602d97022d76b7", "53e9b572b7602d97040b0350", "53e9b239b7602d9703cd550a", "53e9b587b7602d97040c7931", "53e99c30b7602d97024e07d2", "53e9ab3db7602d97034ca179", "53e9b4a1b7602d9703facffd", "53e99ef4b7602d97027c0781", "53e9b69db7602d97042137a7", "53e997c2b7602d9701faec0b"]}

{"id": "53e99837b7602d970205e64c", "title": "Neuronal intestinal dysplasia ", "authors": [{"name": "Prem Puri"}], "venue": "Journal of Pediatric Surgery", "year": 1992, "keywords": ["megacolon", "neuronal intestinal dysplasia", "aganglionosis- hirschsprung' s disease- dysganglionosis"], "n_citation": 33, "page_start": "1477", "page_end": "1477", "lang": "en", "volume": "27", "issue": "11", "issn": "Journal of Pediatric Surgery", "doi": "10.1016/0022-3468(92)90230-5", "url": ["http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/0022-3468(92)90230-5"], "abstract": "Neuronal intestinal dysplasia (NID) is an inhibitory malformation of the submucous and myenteric plexuses. The diagnosis is made by examination of mucosal biopsies after histotopochemical reactions for acetylcholinesterase and lactate or succinate dehydrogenase. The rare NID type A is a disorder of the sympathetic nerves and usually leads to obstructive symptoms, diarrhea containing blood and mucus, and occasionally bowel perforation. Colostomy and resection of the affected bowel segment are unavoidable. Type B involves hyperplasia of the submucous plexus. The biopsy technique and criteria for evaluation have been standardized by prominent pathologists; the histochemical characteristics have been analzed morphometrically. Despite virtually uniform clinical symptoms, varying degrees of histochemical involvement may occur. Since maturation of the propulsive activity is possible in all forms, as a general rule a trial of conservative therapy should be made for at least 6 months. Persistent fecal retention with absence of internal sphincter relaxation can be treated successfully in 90% of cases by posterior sphincteromyotomy. Patients with massive rectal dilatation and absent propulsion require resection of the rectum and descending colon, as rectosigmoidectomy is associated with a high incidence of recurrence. The treatment of aganglionosis in combination with NID necessitates a differentiated work-up and set of indications.", "references": ["53e99b95b7602d970243d832", "53e9abd4b7602d970358d687", "53e9ab2cb7602d97034b9fca", "53e9b444b7602d9703f418b7", "53e9a9ebb7602d970334f101", "53e999b4b7602d97021f7643", "53e99d81b7602d970263f6bd", "53e99fb5b7602d970288faac", "53e9b69db7602d970421380c"]}

Structural imaging with MRI and functional imaging techniques, such as positron emission tomography and single photon emission CT, increasingly are used to aid in the differential diagnosis and early detection of dementia. Imaging techniques also can track disease progression over time and may be useful to monitor treatment effects. The most important development in the field over the past decade is the ability to image amyloid in the brain. This technique will revolutionize patient management and care."}

{"id": "53e99837b7602d970205e652", "title": "Neighborhood income distributions", "authors": [{"name": "Yannis M. Ioannides", "org": "Department of Economics, Tufts University, Medford, MA 02155, USA"}], "venue": "Journal of Urban Economics", "year": 2004, "keywords": ["neighborhood income distribution", "d31", "neighborhood eects", "nonlinear kernel estimation", "neighborhood effects", "income distribution", "income sorting", "c14"], "n_citation": 74, "page_start": "435", "page_end": "457", "lang": "en", "volume": "56", "issue": "3", "issn": "Journal of Urban Economics", "doi": "10.1016/j.jue.2004.04.006", "url": ["http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.jue.2004.04.006"], "abstract": "This paper studies purely empirically aspects of the distribution of income within small neighborhoods and contrasts it with the income distribution at higher level of aggregation, such as census tracts and metropolitan areas. It relies on a unique feature of the American Housing Survey, whose 1985, 1989 and 1993 waves provide data for small residential neighborhoods. These consist of a dwelling unit and up to ten of its nearest neighbors. The paper employs several parametric and non-parametric econometric tools to measure income sorting in US residential neighborhoods. It documents the patterns of dependence among neighbors' income and imperfect sorting, with moderate but very significant correlation among incomes of neighbors and of considerable income mixing in US neighborhoods. These results persist even if choice-based sampling and heterogeneity across the sample are accounted for. Neighborhoods associated with a randomly selected renter are more sorted than those associated with an owner even though such owners are more likely to define their neighborhoods.", "references": ["53e9b0bcb7602d9703b2c128", "53e99c5fb7602d970250de39", "53e998b0b7602d97020eb472", "53e99afeb7602d970238d1f0", "53e997f4b7602d9701ff80dd", "53e9afe1b7602d9703a33fdf", "53e9a336b7602d9702c425e2", "53e9a9ebb7602d970334f8d5", "53e9a9e6b7602d970334c812"]}
{"id": "53e99837b7602d970205e653", "title": "Non-invasive densitometry.", "authors": [{"name": "Paul Lips", "org": "Department of Endocrinology, Free University Hospital, P.O. Box 7057, 1007 MB Amsterdam, The Netherlands"}], "venue": "Acta astronautica", "year": 1992, "page_start": "83", "page_end": "87", "lang": "en", "volume": "27", "issn": "0094-5765", "doi": "10.1016/0094-5765(92)90181-H", "url": ["http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/0094-5765(92)90181-H", "http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/11537603?report=xml&format=text"], "abstract": "Several non-invasive methods are available to measure bone density in different regions of the skeleton. Bedrest and microgravity both lead to bone loss, which is more marked in the lower parts of the skeleton. The bone loss can be monitored by non-invasive techniques in longitudinal studies when precision (i.e. the ability to produce repeated measurements with the same value) is adequate. Bone mineral density (BMD) can be measured with single photon absorptiometry in the lower forearm and calcaneus and with dual energy X-ray absorptiometry (DXA) in almost any region of the skeleton. The latter technique pairs good precision with very low radiation exposure. With peripheral quantitative computed tomography very precise measurements of the lower forearm and tibia are feasible with low radiation dose. It has the additional option of separate measurement of cortical and trabecular bone. This could be of particular importance in microgravity studies, as trabecular bone loss is more severe in this condition. A new development is the measurement of ultrasound velocity or attenuation which depends on bone density and structure. Ultrasound data of the calcaneus correlate well with bone mineral density in spine and hip. The advantage of this technique is that it operates without radiation. However, the clinical value has to be established. The ultimate choice of technique and skeletal region for bone densitometry will depend on specific requirements.", "references": ["53e9b716b7602d97042ad716", "56d824d8dabfae2eeed583e9", "53e9b8e8b7602d97044cb83d", "53e99e38b7602d97026f8aa6", "53e9a326b7602d9702c31915", "55a44fe02401c6de3b8ec2c4"]}

{"id": "53e99837b7602d970205e657", "title": "NEURITIS IN DIABETES.", "authors": [{"name": "Thomas Buzzard"}], "venue": "The Lancet", "year": 1890, "page_start": "571", "page_end": "571", "lang": "en", "volume": "135", "issue": "3471", "issn": "The Lancet", "doi": "10.1016/S0140-6736(02)18921-5", "url": ["http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/S0140-6736(02)18921-5"]}
{"id": "53e99837b7602d970205e658", "title": "Nutritional iron deficiency", "authors": [{"name": "Michael B Zimmermann"}, {"name": "Richard F Hurrell", "org": "Laboratory for Human Nutrition, Swiss Federal Institute of Technology, Z\u00fcrich, Switzerland"}], "venue": "The Lancet", "year": 2007, "keywords": ["primary health care", "biology", "program design", "developing world", "genetics", "medicine", "physiology", "clinical research", "plant breeding", "iron", "research methodology", "genetic engineering", "evaluation", "risk factors", "health", "protein targeting"], "page_start": "511", "page_end": "520", "lang": "en", "volume": "370", "issue": "9586", "issn": "The Lancet", "doi": "10.1016/S0140-6736(07)61235-5", "url": ["http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/S0140-6736(07)61235-5"], "abstract": "Iron deficiency is one of the leading risk factors for disability and death worldwide, affecting an estimated 2 billion people. Nutritional iron deficiency arises when physiological requirements cannot be met by iron absorption from diet. Dietary iron bioavailability is low in populations consuming monotonous plant-based diets. The high prevalence of iron deficiency in the developing world has substantial health and economic costs, including poor pregnancy outcome, impaired school performance, and decreased productivity. Recent studies have reported how the body regulates iron absorption and metabolism in response to changing iron status by upregulation or downregulation of key intestinal and hepatic proteins. Targeted iron supplementation, iron fortification of foods, or both, can control iron deficiency in populations. Although technical challenges limit the amount of bioavailable iron compounds that can be used in food fortification, studies show that iron fortification can be an effective strategy against nutritional iron deficiency. Specific laboratory measures of iron status should be used to assess the need for fortification and to monitor these interventions. Selective plant breeding and genetic engineering are promising new approaches to improve dietary iron nutritional quality.", "references": ["55a34faa24012c2ab7a5e121", "53e99d5eb7602d970261a8bc", {"id": "53e99837b7602d970205e659", "title": "NEUROIMAGING IN DEMENTIA", "authors": [{"name": "William J. Jagust"}], "venue": "Neurologic Clinics", "year": 2000, "page_start": "885", "page_end": "901", "lang": "en", "volume": "18", "issue": "4", "issn": "Neurologic Clinics", "doi": "10.1016/S0733-8619(05)70231-0"}
{"id": "53e99837b7602d970205e65a", "title": "Neuro-imagerie des\u00a0d\u00e9mences", "authors": [{"name": "St\u00e9phane Leh\u00e9ricy"}, {"name": "Christine Delmaire", "org": "Service de\u00a0neuroradiologie, Centre hospitalo-universitaire, Lille (57)"}, {"name": "Damien Galanaud", "org": "Service de\u00a0neuroradiologie, Centre hospitalo-universitaire Piti\u00e9-Salp\u00eatri\u00e8re, Paris (75)"}, {"name": "Didier Dormont", "org": "CNRS UPR 640, Paris (75)"}], "venue": "La Presse Medicale", "year": 2007, "page_start": "1453", "page_end": "1463", "lang": "en", "volume": "36", "issue": "10", "issn": "La Presse Medicale", "doi": "10.1016/j.lpm.2007.04.029", "abstract": "L'imagerie fait partie du bilan de tout syndrome d\u00e9mentiel. La tomodensitom\u00e9trie \u00e0 rayons X est l'examen de premi\u00e8re intention. Elle \u00e9limine les causes de d\u00e9mences chirurgicales. L'IRM (imagerie par r\u00e9sonance magn\u00e9tique) est pr\u00e9f\u00e9r\u00e9e dans le bilan des d\u00e9mences. Dans les d\u00e9mences neurod\u00e9g\u00e9n\u00e9ratives, elle montre une atrophie dont la topographie oriente vers l'\u00e9tiologie de la d\u00e9mence : une atrophie temporale m\u00e9diale pr\u00e9dominante dans la maladie d'Alzheimer ; une atrophie frontale et temporale ant\u00e9rieure marqu\u00e9e et une atrophie temporale m\u00e9diale moindre que celle d\u00e9crite dans la maladie d'Alzheimer\u00a0dans la d\u00e9mence frontotemporale ; des infarctus, des lacunes, des anomalies de signal de la substance blanche et parfois des microsaignements dans les d\u00e9mences vasculaires. La tomographie \u00e0 \u00e9mission de simples photons (TEMP) et la tomographie \u00e0 \u00e9mission positrons (TEP) sont utilis\u00e9es dans les formes cliniquement atypiques. L'\u00e9tude du transporteur de la dopamine (DATscan \u00ae ) est utilis\u00e9e pour distinguer la d\u00e9mence \u00e0 corps de Lewy de la maladie d'Alzheimer. De nombreux efforts sont d\u00e9ploy\u00e9s pour trouver des biomarqueurs d'imagerie dans les d\u00e9mences, incluant la volum\u00e9trie c\u00e9r\u00e9brale, l'imagerie de diffusion, la spectroscopie, l'imagerie des plaques s\u00e9niles en IRM \u00e0 tr\u00e8s haut champ et les marqueurs des plaques s\u00e9niles en TEP. Glossaire Cadasil Cerebral autosomal dominant arteriopathy with subcortical infarcts and leukoencephalopathy Cho choline Cr cr\u00e9atine DFT d\u00e9mence frontotemporale DVIS d\u00e9mence vasculaire isch\u00e9mique sous-corticale FDG 18 F-2-fluoro-2-d\u00e9oxy-D-glucose HAS Haute autorit\u00e9 de sant\u00e9 IRM imagerie par r\u00e9sonance magn\u00e9tique MCI Mild Cognitive Impairment mI myo-inositol MID Multi-Infarct Dementia MMS Mini-Mental State MSA atrophie multisyst\u00e8me NAA N-ac\u00e9tylaspartate PIB traceur marqu\u00e9 au 11 C PSP paralysie supranucl\u00e9aire progressive SRM spectroscopie par r\u00e9sonance magn\u00e9tique TDM tomodensitom\u00e9trie TEMP tomographie \u00e0 \u00e9mission de simples photons TEP tomographie \u00e0 \u00e9mission positrons La tomodensitom\u00e9trie \u00e0 rayons X (TDM) et l'IRM conventionnelle sont les techniques couramment utilis\u00e9es dans l'exploration d'une d\u00e9mence. Les techniques utilisant des traceurs radioactifs sont r\u00e9serv\u00e9es aux formes cliniquement atypiques. Diff\u00e9rentes techniques d'imagerie Les recommandations de l'Anaes (maintenant remplac\u00e9e par la Haute autorit\u00e9 de sant\u00e9 : HAS) sont les suivantes : \u00ab Une imagerie c\u00e9r\u00e9brale syst\u00e9matique est recommand\u00e9e pour toute d\u00e9mence d'installation r\u00e9cente. Le but de cet examen est de ne pas m\u00e9conna\u00eetre l'existence d'une autre cause de d\u00e9mence (processus expansif intracr\u00e2nien, hydroc\u00e9phalie \u00e0 pression normale, l\u00e9sions d'origine vasculaire, etc.). Il n'est pas recommand\u00e9 d'effectuer une injection de produit de contraste en l'absence d'\u00e9l\u00e9ment pouvant le justifier [\u2026]. Cet examen sera au mieux une imagerie par r\u00e9sonance magn\u00e9tique nucl\u00e9aire, \u00e0 d\u00e9faut une tomodensitom\u00e9trie c\u00e9r\u00e9brale, en fonction de l'accessibilit\u00e9 \u00e0 ces techniques. \u00bb Tomodensitom\u00e9trie \u00e0\u00a0rayons X La TDM reste l'examen de premi\u00e8re intention. Elle est utile pour chercher les causes de d\u00e9mences chirurgicales, des l\u00e9sions vasculaires ou une atrophie. La TDM permet d'\u00e9liminer la plupart des causes de d\u00e9mences chirurgicales : les h\u00e9matomes sous-duraux (d'autant plus qu'ils sont bilat\u00e9raux), certaines tumeurs (comme le classique m\u00e9ningiome fronto-orbitaire), l'hydroc\u00e9phalie \u00e0 pression normale. L'examen TDM sans injection est en r\u00e8gle g\u00e9n\u00e9rale suffisant pour \u00e9liminer la plupart des causes de d\u00e9mences chirurgicales. Il est le plus souvent r\u00e9alis\u00e9 en coupes axiales dans le plan orbitom\u00e9atal qui passe par l'angle externe de l'orbite et le conduit auditif externe. Les meilleurs r\u00e9sultats pour l'exploration d'une maladie d'Alzheimer sont obtenus dans le plan axial parall\u00e8le au grand axe des hippocampes. Les acquisitions h\u00e9lico\u00efdales des appareils r\u00e9cents permettent de reconstruire les images dans le plan coronal perpendiculaire \u00e0 l'axe des lobes temporaux ( figure\u00a01 ) . Dans la maladie d'Alzheimer, la TDM montre une atrophie c\u00e9r\u00e9brale qui est surtout visible au niveau de la corne ant\u00e9rieure du ventricule lat\u00e9ral au stade pr\u00e9coce de la maladie ( figure\u00a02 ) . Dans les d\u00e9mences vasculaires, le scanner montre des infarctus, des lacunes et/ou des hypodensit\u00e9s importantes de la substance blanche. Imagerie par\u00a0r\u00e9sonance magn\u00e9tique L'HAS pr\u00e9cise \u00e9galement que l'IRM sera pr\u00e9f\u00e9r\u00e9e \u00e0 la TDM quand cela est possible. L'IRM permet une analyse dans tous les plans de l'espace et offre un excellent contraste entre substance grise et substance blanche. C'est un meilleur outil d'analyse de l'atrophie temporale que la TDM. L'IRM va donc permettre de rechercher des signes positifs de d\u00e9mence d\u00e9g\u00e9n\u00e9rative, une meilleure d\u00e9tection des anomalies vasculaires et l'utilisation de plusieurs types de s\u00e9quences comme la spectroscopie ou la diffusion. Actuellement, l'IRM est le plus souvent demand\u00e9e lorsque le diagnostic reste incertain ou avant l'inclusion dans un essai th\u00e9rapeutique. L'examen IRM comprend des images anatomiques pond\u00e9r\u00e9es en T1, des images coronales ou axiales pond\u00e9r\u00e9es en Flair et des images axiales pond\u00e9r\u00e9es en \u00e9cho de gradient T2 (T2*) ( encadr\u00e9\u00a01 ). Les images anatomiques permettent de d\u00e9tecter une atrophie temporale m\u00e9diale (hippocampe, amygdale, r\u00e9gion parahippocampique). Elles sont au mieux r\u00e9alis\u00e9es \u00e0 l'aide de coupes 3D pond\u00e9r\u00e9es en T1 dans le plan coronal perpendiculaire \u00e0 l'axe des lobes temporaux. Des images en haute r\u00e9solution T2 peuvent \u00e9galement \u00eatre utilis\u00e9es. Les images pond\u00e9r\u00e9es en Flair permettent d'\u00e9valuer la pr\u00e9sence d'une atteinte vasculaire Les images pond\u00e9r\u00e9es en T2* sont r\u00e9alis\u00e9es \u00e0 la recherche d'\u00e9ventuels microsaignements dans le cadre d'une d\u00e9mence vasculaire. Des images axiales pond\u00e9r\u00e9es en diffusion peuvent \u00eatre r\u00e9alis\u00e9es pour pr\u00e9ciser le caract\u00e8re r\u00e9cent ou ancien d'anomalies vasculaires. Tomographie \u00e0\u00a0\u00e9mission de\u00a0simples photons La tomographie \u00e0 \u00e9mission monophotonique (TEMP ou SPECT en anglais) de perfusion est utilis\u00e9e dans les formes cliniquement atypiques. Dans la maladie d'Alzheimer, elle montre une hypoperfusion temporopari\u00e9tale [1] . Ces anomalies s'\u00e9tendent avec l'\u00e9volution de la maladie. La TEMP est donc un marqueur topographique et la localisation des anomalies de perfusion contribue \u00e0 distinguer les d\u00e9mences d\u00e9g\u00e9n\u00e9ratives. L'\u00e9tude du transporteur de la dopamine avec le [ 123 I]-FP-CIT (DATscan \u00ae ) est aussi utile pour distinguer la d\u00e9mence \u00e0 corps de Lewy de la maladie d'Alzheimer [2, 3] ( figure\u00a03 ) . Tomographie \u00e0\u00a0\u00e9mission positrons La tomographie \u00e0 \u00e9mission de positrons (TEP) au 18 F-2-fluoro-2-d\u00e9oxy-D-glucose (FDG) permet une mesure de la consommation r\u00e9gionale de glucose. La consommation de glucose est un reflet du m\u00e9tabolisme neuronal. Comme la TEMP, la TEP est utilis\u00e9e dans les formes cliniquement atypiques [1, 4] . Dans la maladie d'Alzheimer, une r\u00e9duction du m\u00e9tabolisme est d\u00e9tect\u00e9e t\u00f4t. Elle touche les aires associatives n\u00e9ocorticales (cortex cingulaire post\u00e9rieur, cortex temporopari\u00e9tal et frontal multimodal), alors que les r\u00e9gions visuelles et sensorimotrices, les ganglions de la base et le cervelet sont relativement pr\u00e9serv\u00e9s [5] . Les anomalies sont d\u00e9celables chez les patients \u00e0 haut risque g\u00e9n\u00e9tique et encore asymptomatiques [6] . La TEP au FDG est un examen facile \u00e0 r\u00e9aliser et bien tol\u00e9r\u00e9 chez les patients. Imagerie des\u00a0principaux types de\u00a0d\u00e9mences D\u00e9mences neurod\u00e9g\u00e9n\u00e9ratives Maladie d'Alzheimer La maladie d'Alzheimer est la cause de d\u00e9mence d\u00e9g\u00e9n\u00e9rative la plus fr\u00e9quente. Au stade pr\u00e9coce de la maladie d'Alzheimer, l'imagerie va rechercher une atrophie localis\u00e9e aux r\u00e9gions temporales m\u00e9diales [7] ( figure\u00a04 ) . \u00c0 ce stade, l'atrophie temporale m\u00e9diale est difficile \u00e0 mettre en \u00e9vidence visuellement et l'examen peut para\u00eetre normal. Un examen en apparence normal ne permet donc pas d'\u00e9liminer le diagnostic de maladie d'Alzheimer. L'exp\u00e9rience de l'examinateur est alors un facteur important. En cas de doute, il est possible de r\u00e9p\u00e9ter l'examen. Une atrophie temporale m\u00e9diale d'\u00e9volution rapide sur 2 examens successifs est tr\u00e8s \u00e9vocatrice de maladie d'Alzheimer [7-9] ( figure\u00a05 ) . Au stade avanc\u00e9 de la maladie, l'imagerie standard qualitative (TDM ou IRM) montre une atrophie c\u00e9r\u00e9brale globale ou \u00e0 pr\u00e9dominance temporale et parfois des anomalies de signal non sp\u00e9cifiques de la substance blanche sus-tentorielle (hypodensit\u00e9s TDM ou hypersignaux sur les s\u00e9quences IRM pond\u00e9r\u00e9es en T2). D\u00e9mence \u00e0\u00a0corps de\u00a0Lewy La d\u00e9mence \u00e0 corps de Lewy constituerait la cause de d\u00e9mences neurod\u00e9g\u00e9n\u00e9ratives la plus fr\u00e9quente apr\u00e8s la maladie d'Alzheimer, avec une fr\u00e9quence comprise entre 15 \u00e0 25 % [3] . L'atrophie est trouv\u00e9e dans les r\u00e9gions limbiques, le n\u00e9ocortex et les structures sous-corticales avec une relative pr\u00e9servation des structures temporales m\u00e9diales par rapport \u00e0 la maladie d'Alzheimer [10] . Dans la d\u00e9mence \u00e0 corps de Lewy, il existe une atrophie hippocampique, mais celle-ci reste inf\u00e9rieure \u00e0 celle observ\u00e9e dans la maladie d'Alzheimer [11] . L'atrophie hippocampique n'est pas discriminante entre les 2 pathologies, mais son absence va \u00e0 l'encontre du diagnostic de maladie d'Alzheimer. Le DATscan \u00ae est utile pour distinguer la d\u00e9mence \u00e0 corps de Lewy de la maladie d'Alzheimer [2, 3] . Il montre une baisse bilat\u00e9rale du marquage du transporteur de la dopamine dans le striatum de ces patients ( figure\u00a03 ) . D\u00e9mence frontotemporale La d\u00e9mence frontotemporale (DFT) constituerait la troisi\u00e8me cause de d\u00e9mence neurod\u00e9g\u00e9n\u00e9rative [12] . L'histologie trouve 2 causes principales : le plus souvent des signes de d\u00e9g\u00e9n\u00e9rescence non sp\u00e9cifique, et moins fr\u00e9quemment une maladie de Pick [13] . Dans la DFT, les l\u00e9sions pr\u00e9dominent dans les r\u00e9gions ant\u00e9rieures du lobe frontal et du lobe temporal, \u00e9pargnant relativement les r\u00e9gions temporales m\u00e9diales ( figure\u00a06 ) . Il existe une atrophie bilat\u00e9rale des hippocampes et du cortex entorhinal qui pr\u00e9domine sur la partie ant\u00e9rieure. Un hypersignal Flair des r\u00e9gions ant\u00e9rieures est fr\u00e9quent. Comparativement \u00e0 la maladie d'Alzheimer, la DFT se caract\u00e9rise par une atrophie frontale et temporale ant\u00e9rieure plus marqu\u00e9e et une atrophie temporale m\u00e9diale moins s\u00e9v\u00e8re. L'imagerie TEMP montre une hypoperfusion frontale et temporale ant\u00e9rieure qui peut \u00eatre pr\u00e9sente alors que l'atrophie est peu marqu\u00e9e. D\u00e9mences avec\u00a0syndromes parkinsoniens La d\u00e9mence\u00a0dans la maladie de parkinson survient tardivement au cours du suivi \u00e9volutif chez\u00a0environ 40 % des patients. Dans la maladie de Parkinson avec d\u00e9mence, 3 groupes de l\u00e9sions histologiques sont retrouv\u00e9s : sous-corticales (monoaminergiques et cholinergiques), de type Alzheimer, et de type corps de Lewy [14] . Les l\u00e9sions pr\u00e9dominantes seraient plut\u00f4t proches de celles de la d\u00e9mence \u00e0 corps de Lewy. En IRM, l'aspect se rapprocherait de celui observ\u00e9 dans la d\u00e9mence \u00e0 corps de Lewy [15] . Les syndromes parkinsoniens atypiques regroupent la paralysie supranucl\u00e9aire progressive (PSP) et les atrophies multisyst\u00e8mes (MSA) [14, 16] . Comme la d\u00e9mence n'est pas consid\u00e9r\u00e9e comme un crit\u00e8re diagnostique des MSA [17] , celles-ci ne seront pas discut\u00e9es ici. Dans la PSP, l'atrophie pr\u00e9domine au niveau du m\u00e9senc\u00e9phale avec un aspect caract\u00e9ristique sur les vues sagittales [18] ( figure\u00a07 ) . Une atrophie corticale est aussi pr\u00e9sente [19] . D\u00e9mences vasculaires Les d\u00e9mences vasculaires repr\u00e9sentent la seconde cause de d\u00e9mence aux \u00c9tats-Unis et en Europe, apr\u00e8s la maladie d'Alzheimer, soit environ 10-30 % des cas [20] . Les d\u00e9mences vasculaires sont maintenant consid\u00e9r\u00e9es comme un ensemble h\u00e9t\u00e9rog\u00e8ne incluant des l\u00e9sions c\u00e9r\u00e9brovasculaires vari\u00e9es : isch\u00e9mique, hypoperfusive et h\u00e9morragique. D\u00e9mence multi-infarctus La d\u00e9mence multi-infarctus ( Multi-Infarct Dementia [MID]) refl\u00e8te la conception classique de la d\u00e9mence vasculaire typiquement caract\u00e9ris\u00e9e par la pr\u00e9sence d'infarctus corticaux et sous-corticaux multiples de grande taille dans des territoires art\u00e9riels ou de jonction [21] ( figure\u00a08 ) . Ce n'est pas la forme la plus fr\u00e9quente [20] . D\u00e9mence par\u00a0infarctus strat\u00e9giques La d\u00e9mence par infarctus strat\u00e9giques est caract\u00e9ris\u00e9e par la pr\u00e9sence de l\u00e9sions isch\u00e9miques focales de petite taille situ\u00e9es dans des r\u00e9gions sp\u00e9cifiques du cerveau dont le r\u00f4le est critique pour les fonctions cognitives sup\u00e9rieures [22] . Les r\u00e9gions corticales concern\u00e9es sont le lobe temporal m\u00e9dial, les gyri angulaire et cingulaire. Les r\u00e9gions sous-corticales incluent certains territoires du thalamus, la base de l'enc\u00e9phale, le noyau caud\u00e9, le globus pallidus, le genou et le bras ant\u00e9rieur de la capsule interne. D\u00e9mence vasculaire isch\u00e9mique sous-corticale Dans la d\u00e9mence vasculaire isch\u00e9mique sous-corticale (DVIS) (ou Subcortical Ischaemic Vascular Dementia [SIVD]), deux types de l\u00e9sions sont rencontr\u00e9s : l'occlusion d'une petite art\u00e8re par ath\u00e9roscl\u00e9rose conduisant \u00e0 la formation d'une lacune dont la r\u00e9p\u00e9tition aboutit \u00e0 l'\u00e9tat lacunaire, et l'hypoperfusion chronique par st\u00e9nose des petites art\u00e8res responsable d'infarctus incomplets de la substance blanche profonde. La DVIS comporte des lacunes et des l\u00e9sions focales ou diffuses de la substance blanche [23] . Les l\u00e9sions de la substance blanche sont visibles sous forme d'hypodensit\u00e9s (TDM) ou d'hypersignaux T2 et Flair (IRM) bilat\u00e9raux et sym\u00e9triques de la substance blanche p\u00e9riventriculaire ou sous-corticale ( figure\u00a09 ) . Les l\u00e9sions de la substance blanche sont volontiers d\u00e9crites sous le terme radiologique de \u201cleucoara\u00efose\u201d ( leuco = blanc et ara\u00efose = rar\u00e9faction), terme propos\u00e9 par Hachinski [24] . Il s'agit d'un terme non sp\u00e9cifique qui d\u00e9crit les anomalies focales ou diffuses de la substance blanche. La leucoara\u00efose ne traduit pas une l\u00e9sion histopathologique d\u00e9finie. Elle regroupe des l\u00e9sions histologiques multiples, comme les lacunes, les l\u00e9sions isch\u00e9miques incompl\u00e8tes, la gliose. Selon les crit\u00e8res internationaux dans la DVIS [23] , la TDM doit montrer des l\u00e9sions extensives de la substance blanche p\u00e9riventriculaire et profonde, visibles sous la forme d'hypodensit\u00e9s focales ou diffuses \u00e0 contours mal d\u00e9finis \u00e9tendues au centre ovale et au moins une lacune sous-corticale. L'IRM doit montrer : \u2022 des hyperintensit\u00e9s de la substance blanche p\u00e9riventriculaire et profonde , en couronne autour des ventricules (>10\u00a0mm) ou en halo irr\u00e9gulier (>10\u00a0mm avec des bords larges et irr\u00e9guliers et \u00e9tendues dans la substance blanche profonde) et des hyperintensit\u00e9s confluentes (>25\u00a0mm, irr\u00e9guli\u00e8res) ou des anomalies diffuses sans l\u00e9sions focales et une ou des lacunes sous-corticales ; \u2022 ou des lacunes multiples (>\u00a05\u00a0mm) des noyaux gris et au moins des l\u00e9sions mod\u00e9r\u00e9es de la substance blanche ; \u2022 l'absence d'autre cause (h\u00e9morragie, v\u00e9ritables infarctus, l\u00e9sions inflammatoires, etc.). D\u00e9mences h\u00e9morragiques Certaines d\u00e9mences vasculaires, comme le Cadasil ( Cerebral autosomal dominant Arteriopathy with subcortical infarcts and leukoencephalopathy ), l'angiopathie amylo\u00efde ou la sid\u00e9rose superficielle pr\u00e9sentent des h\u00e9matomes intrac\u00e9r\u00e9braux multiples [23] . En IRM, les l\u00e9sions h\u00e9morragiques chroniques sont caract\u00e9ris\u00e9es par la pr\u00e9sence de d\u00e9p\u00f4ts d'h\u00e9mosid\u00e9rine tr\u00e8s hypointense sur les s\u00e9quences pond\u00e9r\u00e9es en \u00e9cho de gradient T2. D\u00e9mence mixte vasculaire et\u00a0Alzheimer La distinction clinique entre maladie d'Alzheimer avec l\u00e9sions c\u00e9r\u00e9brovasculaires associ\u00e9es et d\u00e9mence vasculaire peut \u00eatre difficile [23] . De nombreux facteurs de risque vasculaires sont communs et le mode de d\u00e9but des troubles des 2 types de d\u00e9mences n'est parfois pas typique. Plus de 60 % des patients avec maladie d'Alzheimer pr\u00e9sentent des l\u00e9sions de la substance blanche sous-corticale ou profonde [25] . Ces l\u00e9sions sont cependant moins marqu\u00e9es que dans les d\u00e9mences vasculaires. L'atrophie temporale m\u00e9diale qui est une des caract\u00e9ristiques de la maladie d'Alzheimer a \u00e9t\u00e9 d\u00e9crite dans les d\u00e9mences vasculaires [26] . En r\u00e8gle g\u00e9n\u00e9rale, elle est moins marqu\u00e9e que dans la maladie d'Alzheimer. La progression de l'atrophie au cours du temps est \u00e9galement plus marqu\u00e9e dans la d\u00e9mence vasculaire que chez les sujets \u00e2g\u00e9s normaux [20] . Voies de\u00a0recherche De nombreux efforts sont d\u00e9ploy\u00e9s pour trouver des biomarqueurs d'imagerie dans les d\u00e9mences. Ces biomarqueurs serviraient \u00e0 pr\u00e9dire l'\u00e9volution vers la d\u00e9mence au stade pr\u00e9d\u00e9mentiel ou chez les sujets \u00e0 risque, \u00e9valuer l'efficacit\u00e9 de th\u00e9rapeutiques potentielles et comprendre la physiopathologie de cette maladie (localisation et progression des l\u00e9sions c\u00e9r\u00e9brales, corr\u00e9lations clinico-anatomiques et fonctionnelles). Plusieurs pistes sont explor\u00e9es [8, 9, 27-29] . Volum\u00e9trie IRM Certains centres sp\u00e9cialis\u00e9s ont recours \u00e0 des techniques de quantification de l'atrophie, notamment temporale m\u00e9diale [27, 28] . Les mesures volum\u00e9triques permettent de quantifier l'atrophie temporale m\u00e9diale , qui est une caract\u00e9ristique pr\u00e9coce de la maladie d'Alzheimer. Les mesures de volume ont permis de montrer que l'hippocampe \u00e9tait r\u00e9duit d'environ 40 % dans les formes mod\u00e9r\u00e9es de la maladie d'Alzheimer, 25 % dans les formes l\u00e9g\u00e8res (MMS = Mini-Mental State > 20) et 10-15 % dans le MCI ( Mild Cognitive Impairment ) [30, 31] . Le taux annuel d'atrophie a \u00e9t\u00e9 \u00e9valu\u00e9 entre 2 et 6 % chez les patients Alzheimer pour moins de 1 % chez les sujets sains \u00e2g\u00e9s [31, 32] . La sensibilit\u00e9 des mesures est en g\u00e9n\u00e9ral > 90 % pour distinguer patients et sujets \u00e2g\u00e9s sains et baisse \u00e0 70-80 % dans le MCI. La sp\u00e9cificit\u00e9 par rapport aux autres d\u00e9mences d\u00e9g\u00e9n\u00e9ratives est nettement plus faible. Ces techniques ne sont pas encore r\u00e9pandues car elles sont longues et pas encore automatis\u00e9es. L'atrophie hippocampique est sp\u00e9cifiquement corr\u00e9l\u00e9e avec les scores des \u00e9preuves de m\u00e9moire. Spectroscopie par\u00a0r\u00e9sonance magn\u00e9tique La spectroscopie par r\u00e9sonance magn\u00e9tique (SRM) procure des informations sur le m\u00e9tabolisme c\u00e9r\u00e9bral. Les deux principaux m\u00e9tabolites utiles dans la maladie d'Alzheimer sont le N-ac\u00e9tylaspartate (NAA) et le myo-inositol (mI). Le NAA est consid\u00e9r\u00e9 comme un marqueur des neurones. Il baisse en cas de mort ou de souffrance neuronale. Le mI est pr\u00e9sent dans les cellules gliales. Il est consid\u00e9r\u00e9 comme un marqueur du stress osmotique et de la gliose. La SRM peut \u00eatre r\u00e9alis\u00e9e dans le cadre d'un examen IRM conventionnel. Elle vient en compl\u00e9ment de l'imagerie morphologique et apporte des renseignements sur le m\u00e9tabolisme c\u00e9r\u00e9bral. Dans la maladie d'Alzheimer, il existe une diminution du NAA et une augmentation du mI [9, 33] . Le rapport NAA/mI diminue en particulier dans les r\u00e9gions temporales m\u00e9diales ( figure\u00a010 ) . La baisse du NAA s'accro\u00eet avec l'\u00e9volution de la maladie. Les modifications sont pr\u00e9coces. Elles seraient corr\u00e9l\u00e9es \u00e0 la baisse des fonctions cognitives. Les patterns d'alt\u00e9rations m\u00e9taboliques de la maladie d'Alzheimer pourraient diff\u00e9rer de celui des d\u00e9mences vasculaires (rapport myoinositol/cr\u00e9atine (mI/Cr) sup\u00e9rieur dans la maladie d'Alzheimer) [34] mais cela n'est pas constant. Dans la PSP, une baisse du rapport NAA/Cr ou NAA/Cho (choline) a \u00e9t\u00e9 rapport\u00e9e dans le noyau lenticulaire [35] . Imagerie de\u00a0diffusion L'imagerie de diffusion est sensible aux mouvements thermiques al\u00e9atoires des mol\u00e9cules d'eau dans les tissus [36] . Une augmentation de la diffusivit\u00e9 pourrait traduire des modifications de l'organisation ultrastructurelle du cerveau ou bien \u00eatre secondaire \u00e0 l'atrophie neuronale. La diffusion de l'eau peut aussi pr\u00e9senter un certain degr\u00e9 d'orientation, variable selon les tissus et surtout pr\u00e9sente dans la substance blanche. Cette propri\u00e9t\u00e9 est appel\u00e9e anisotropie. Une baisse de l'anisotropie refl\u00e9terait une alt\u00e9ration des faisceaux de fibres de substance blanche qui connectent des r\u00e9gions du cerveau touch\u00e9es par la maladie. Dans la maladie d'Alzheimer et chez les patients MCI, la diffusivit\u00e9 est augment\u00e9e dans le lobe temporal et la substance blanche des r\u00e9gions post\u00e9rieures du cerveau [37, 38] . L'anisotropie est en revanche diminu\u00e9e dans plusieurs r\u00e9gions c\u00e9r\u00e9brales comme le corps calleux, le cingulum, le faisceau longitudinal sup\u00e9rieur ou le faisceau perforant [39] . Une diffusivit\u00e9 \u00e9lev\u00e9e dans l'hippocampe chez un patient MCI est associ\u00e9e \u00e0 un risque de conversion plus \u00e9lev\u00e9 vers la maladie d'Alzheimer [37] Ces mesures pourraient donc avoir un int\u00e9r\u00eat diagnostique dans la maladie d'Alzheimer. Microscopie IRM L'IRM \u00e0 tr\u00e8s haut champ (\u2265\u00a07 T) permet d'obtenir des images dont la r\u00e9solution spatiale est suffisante pour voir les plaques s\u00e9niles. On parle alors de microscopie IRM. Chez l'animal, les plaques apparaissent comme des taches sombres arrondies sur les s\u00e9quences pond\u00e9r\u00e9es en T2, probablement parce qu'elles contiennent des m\u00e9taux comme le fer [40] . Ces m\u00e9thodes ne sont pas encore applicables \u00e0 l'homme car les temps d'acquisition des images sont \u00e0 l'heure actuelle trop longs, bien que les temps d'acquisition des \u00e9tudes r\u00e9centes s'approchent des limites raisonnables chez l'homme. Elles restent en outre limit\u00e9es \u00e0 la disponibilit\u00e9 de ce type d'appareils IRM car peu d'exemplaires sont install\u00e9s dans le monde. Tomographie \u00e0\u00a0\u00e9mission de\u00a0positrons L'\u00e9laboration r\u00e9cente de nouveaux traceurs radioactifs sp\u00e9cifiques de la prot\u00e9ine amylo\u00efde (dont le PIB, un d\u00e9riv\u00e9 de la thioflavine) permet maintenant d'obtenir des informations quantitatives sur la pr\u00e9sence des d\u00e9p\u00f4ts amylo\u00efdes dans le cerveau. Le PIB est un traceur marqu\u00e9 au 11 C \u00e9labor\u00e9 par l'universit\u00e9 de Pittsburgh, \u00e9galement connu sous le nom de Pittsburgh Compound-B. Ce traceur marque les plaques chez la souris transg\u00e9nique et plus r\u00e9cemment chez l'homme [41] . Plusieurs cas de patients remplissant les crit\u00e8res de maladie d'Alzheimer mais sans marquage PIB et inversement de sujets sains pr\u00e9sentant un marquage au PIB ont \u00e9t\u00e9 rapport\u00e9s sans qu'on en connaisse \u00e0 l'heure actuelle la raison [42, 43] . La progression de l'atrophie corticale globale annuelle est corr\u00e9l\u00e9e au taux de fixation du PIB. Il n'y a pas de corr\u00e9lation franche entre l'\u00e9volution du score au MMS et la fixation du PIB en TEP. La technique est donc en cours d'\u00e9valuation et son int\u00e9r\u00eat diagnostique est \u00e9lev\u00e9 [29] . Conflits d'int\u00e9r\u00eats : aucun R\u00e9f\u00e9rences 1 W. {"id": "53e99837b7602d970205e65d", "title": "Nuclear isospin diffusivity", "authors": [{"name": "L. Shi", "org": "National Superconducting Cyclotron Laboratory|Department of Physics and Astronomy|Michigan State University"}, {"name": "P. Danielewicz", "org": "National Superconducting Cyclotron Laboratory|Department of Physics and Astronomy|Michigan State University"}], "venue": "Physical Review C", "year": 2003, "n_citation": 99, "lang": "en", "volume": "68", "issue": "6", "doi": "10.1103/PhysRevC.68.064604", "url": ["http://dx.doi.org/10.1103/PhysRevC.68.064604"], "abstract": "The isospin diffusion and other irreversible phenomena are discussed for a\ntwo-component nuclear Fermi system. The set of Boltzmann transport equations,\nsuch as employed for reactions, are linearized, for weak deviations of a system\nfrom uniformity, in order to arrive at nonreversible fluxes linear in the\nnonuniformities. Besides the diffusion driven by a concentration gradient, also\nthe diffusion driven by temperature and pressure gradients is considered.\nDiffusivity, conductivity, heat conduction and shear viscosity coefficients are\nformally expressed in terms of the responses of distribution functions to the\nnonuniformities. The linearized Boltzmann-equation set is solved, under the\napproximation of constant form-factors in the distribution-function responses,\nto find concrete expressions for the transport coefficients in terms of\nweighted collision integrals. The coefficients are calculated numerically for\nnuclear matter, using experimental nucleon-nucleon cross sections. The isospin\ndiffusivity is inversely proportional to the neutron-proton cross section and\nis also sensitive to the symmetry energy. At low temperatures in symmetric\nmatter, the diffusivity is directly proportional to the symmetry energy.", "references": ["53e9a388b7602d9702c96536", "53e9a6c3b7602d9702ff5a78", "53e99d13b7602d97025c846d", "53e99833b7602d97020592d6"]}
{"id": "53e99837b7602d970205e65e", "title": "NegativeCycleDetection in DynamicGraphs", "authors": [{"name": "Nitin Chandrachoodan"}, {"name": "K. J. Ray Liu"}], "lang": "en", "abstract": "We examine the problem of detecting negative cycles in a dynamic graph, which is a fundamental problem that arises in electronic design automation and systems theory (1, 2, 3, 4). Previous approaches used for this have tried to modify Dijkstra's algorithm since it is the fastest known Single-Source Shortest Path algorithm. We introduce the concept of batch mode negative cycle detection, in which a graph changes over time, and negative cycle detection needs to be done periodically. Such scenarios arise, for example, during iterative de- sign space exploration for hardware and software synthesis. We present an algorithm for this problem, based on the Bellman-Ford algorithm, which outperforms previous approaches. We also show that this technique leads to very fast algorithms for the computation of the maximum-cycle mean (MCM) of a graph, especially for a certain form ofsparsegraph. Such sparseness often occurs in practice, as demonstrated for example by the ISCAS 89/93 benchmarks. We present experimental results that demonstrate the advantages of our batch-processing techniques, and illustrate their application to design- space exploration by developing an automated local-search technique for multiple-voltage scheduling of iterative data-flow graphs.", "references": ["53e9bdfdb7602d9704ab10e2", "53e9ac76b7602d970364b00f", "53e9bc9eb7602d970491e998", "53e997e8b7602d9701fe0fe5", "53e99eb5b7602d9702782b23", "53e9bc00b7602d970485b7c3", "53e99a98b7602d970230e1ff", "53e99c91b7602d9702542f64", "53e9b641b7602d970419bc3f", "53e9a17fb7602d9702a751f4"]}

This might be because it is reluctant to accept newcomers into an already established neural network, rather than because potential progenitors are absent. Neural stem cells are a focus of strong interest because of the possibility that they could be used to replace neurons that have been damaged or lost \u2014 perhaps as a result of injury such as trauma or stroke, or through neurodegenerative disorders such as Parkinson's disease. These stem cells can give rise to neurons and their supporting cells, glia, and it is hoped that something akin to neural stem cells in the adult human brain could be stimulated to generate replacement neurons."}

Twelve children had Hirschsprung's disease that masked the existence of proximal NID. In all cases the diagnosis was established by histological-histochemical examination. Amelioration of symptoms by conservative treatment alone was achieved in 4 children; in 13 cases colostomy was necessary. In 6 patients colon resection was performed: 2 suffered from both colitis and obstruction; the other 4 were treated for obstruction, multiple perforations, persistant adynamia of the left colon, and fistulation. In 9 patients the colostomy was closed. Four of 6 children who did not have sonographic confirmation of motility had complications due to colon dysmotility after closure of their normally functioning colostomy. Therapeutic measures are based exclusively on clinical and functional parameters. The clinical picture dictates the emergency measures (colostomy, colon resection, and colectomy). Normal colostomy function is not a sufficient criterion of normal colon motility. Functional sonography of the colon is included in the planning of further therapy. Indications, timing, and extent of colon resection can be reliably determined using the sonographic method.", "references": ["53e99d81b7602d970263f6bd", "53e9ae04b7602d9703810c20", "53e9b69db7602d970421380c", "53e9a073b7602d970295cdfd"]}

{"id": "53e99838b7602d970205e67e", "title": "Nimesulide in dysmenorrhoea.", "authors": [{"name": "M. In dysmenorrhoeic patients, resting pressure is high only in the fundus. Nimesulide reduces the pressure during the maximal but not during the submaximal pain period, with concomitant alleviation of pain. The drug changes the painful state of uterine contracture to painless cyclic contractions. With a single oral dose of 100mg, nimesulide is evenly distributed in female genital tissues (uterine fundus and cervix, oviduct and ovaries), reaching peak concentrations and peak plasma: tissue ratio (0.5) 3 hours after administration. Tissue concentrations range from 0.3 to 1.8 micrograms/g. Two 100mg oral doses of nimesulide administered to dysmenorrhoeic women in a double-blind placebo-controlled cross-over study reduced prostaglandin F2 alpha levels in menstrual blood from 382 to 94 micrograms/L. {"id": "53e99838b7602d970205e68f", "title": "Neuroimaging in Dementia", "authors": [{"name": "maria carmela tartaglia"}, {"name": "paolo vitali"}, {"name": "raffaella migliaccio"}, {"name": "federica agosta"}, {"name": "howard j rosen"}], "year": 2011, "keywords": ["pet", "alzheimer's disease", "mri", "frontotemporal dementia.", "dementia"], "n_citation": 94, "page_start": "82", "page_end": "92", "lang": "en", "volume": "8", "issue": "1", "doi": "10.1007/s13311-010-0012-2", "url": ["http://dx.doi.org/10.1007/s13311-010-0012-2"], "abstract": "Summary\u00a0\u00a0Dementia is a common illness with an incidence that is rising as the aged population increases. There are a number of neurodegenerative\n diseases that cause dementia, including Alzheimer\u2019s disease, dementia with Lewy bodies, and frontotemporal dementia, which\n is subdivided into the behavioral variant, the semantic variant, and nonfluent variant. Numerous other neurodegenerative illnesses\n have an associated dementia, including corticobasal degeneration, Creutzfeldt\u2013Jakob disease, Huntington\u2019s disease, progressive\n supranuclear palsy, multiple system atrophy, Parkinson\u2019s disease dementia, and amyotrophic lateral sclerosis. Vascular dementia\n and AIDS dementia are secondary dementias. Diagnostic criteria have relied on a constellation of symptoms, but the definite\n diagnosis remains a pathologic one. As treatments become available and target specific molecular abnormalities, differentiating\n amongst the various primary dementias early on becomes essential. The role of imaging in dementia has traditionally been directed\n at ruling out treatable and reversible etiologies and not to use imaging to better understand the pathophysiology of the different\n dementias. Different brain imaging techniques allow the examination of the structure, biochemistry, metabolic state, and functional\n capacity of the brain. All of the major neurodegenerative disorders have relatively specific imaging findings that can be\n identified. New imaging techniques carry the hope of revolutionizing the diagnosis of neurodegenerative disease so as to obtain\n a complete molecular, structural, and metabolic characterization, which could be used to improve diagnosis and to stage each\n patient and follow disease progression and response to treatment. {"id": "53e99838b7602d970205e690", "title": "Norovirusinfektionen in Deutschland", "authors": [{"name": "J. Koch", "org": "Robert Koch-Institut Berlin Berlin"}, {"name": "T. Schneider", "org": "Charit\u00e9 Berlin Berlin"}, {"name": "K. Stark", "org": "Robert Koch-Institut Berlin Berlin"}, {"name": "E. Schreier", "org": "Robert Koch-Institut Berlin Berlin"}], "venue": "Bundesgesundheitsblatt-gesundheitsforschung-gesundheitsschutz", "year": 2006, "n_citation": 2, "page_start": "296", "page_end": "309", "lang": "en", "volume": "49", "issue": "3", "doi": "10.1007/s00103-006-1231-x", "url": ["http://dx.doi.org/10.1007/s00103-006-1231-x"], "abstract": "Zusammenfassung\u00a0\u00a0Noroviren verursachen einen Gro\u00dfteil der weltweit auftretenden akuten viralen Gastroenteritiden. Sie verbreiten sich \u00fcber kontaminierte Lebensmittel und Wasser, als Schmierinfektion oder \u00fcber Aerosole, die beim Erbrechen entstehen. Aufgrund der hohen Viruskonzentration im Stuhl oder Erbrochenen, ihrer hohen Umweltstabilit\u00e4t, der niedrigen infekti\u00f6sen Dosis sowie dem Fehlen einer l\u00e4ngerfristigen Immunit\u00e4t f\u00fchren Noroviruserkrankungen neben sporadischen Einzelerkrankungen \u00fcberwiegend in Gemeinschaftseinrichtungen wie Krankenh\u00e4usern und Altenheimen zu Ausbr\u00fcchen von beachtlichem Ausma\u00df. Die Bew\u00e4ltigung dieser Krankheitsgeschehen erfordert ein striktes Hygienemanagement. Kinder und alte Menschen sind von der Erkrankung, die durch pl\u00f6tzlich einsetzendes h\u00e4ufig schwallartiges Erbrechen gekennzeichnet ist, besonders betroffen. Kennzeichnend f\u00fcr Noroviren ist die extreme Genomvariabilit\u00e4t, durch die fortlaufend neue Virusvarianten mit einem unterschiedlich stark ausgepr\u00e4gten pathogenen Potenzial entstehen. Abh\u00e4ngig von der zirkulierenden Virusvariante differiert dadurch vor allem der Wintergipfel der saisonal verlaufenden Erkrankung deutlich. F\u00fcr die Diagnostik stehen neben dem elektronenmikroskopischen Nachweis insbesondere der virale RNA-Nachweis in der PCR bzw. des viralen Antigens im Antigen-Enzymimmunoassay (EIA) zur Verf\u00fcgung. Die Genomsequenzierung liefert wertvolle Informationen zur Identifikation der Virusvariante und zur Aufkl\u00e4rung von Infektionsketten. Erst nach Umsetzung des Infektionsschutzgesetzes (IfSG) im Januar 2001 mit Einf\u00fchrung der Meldepflicht von Norovirusinfektionen ist es m\u00f6glich, einen detaillierten \u00dcberblick zur bundesweiten Epidemiologie dieser Erkrankung in Deutschland zu erhalten.", "references": ["53e99b50b7602d97023f41f3", "53e9ac12b7602d97035d5c4b", "53e9a73cb7602d9703072a14", "53e9b388b7602d9703e68c8d"]}

A broad spectrum of particles, extending from various lipid nanostructures such as liposomes and solid lipid nanoparticles, to metal, nanocrystalline and polymer particles have already been tested as drug delivery systems in different animal models with remarkable results, promising an extensive commercialization in the coming years. Controlled drug release to skin and skin appendages, targeting of hair follicle-specific cell populations, transcutaneous vaccination and transdermal gene therapy are only a few of these new applications. Carrier systems of the new generation take advantage of improved skin penetration properties, depot effect with sustained drug release and of surface functionalization (e.g., the binding to specific ligands) allowing specific cellular and subcellular targeting. Drug delivery to skin by means of microparticles and nanocarriers could revolutionize the treatment of several skin disorders. However, the toxicological and environmental safety of micro- and nanoparticles has to be evaluated using specific toxicological studies prior to a wider implementation of the new technology. This review aims to give an overview of the most investigated applications of transcutaneously applied particle-based formulations in the fields of cosmetics and dermatology.", "references": {"id": "53e99838b7602d970205e694", "title": "Narrator in Drama", "authors": [{"name": "CHEN Jun", "org": "School of Literature,Nanjing University,Nanjing ,China"}], "venue": "Journal of Harbin Institute of Technology(Social Sciences Edition)", "year": 2008, "keywords": ["character narrator", "narrator", "drama", "the second text narrator"], "n_citation": 2, "page_start": "123", "page_end": "128", "lang": "zh", "issue": "05", "abstract": "From the beginning of new age,scholars used formalism,which used narratology for reference,to research drama.Narratology is a literarily theory which is summarized from fictions.If we want to study the narration form of drama,it is inappropriate to use narratology directly,some changes should be made.In fiction text,there are two types of narrators: first person narrator and the third person narrator.The third person narrator exists only in direct speech.When the all-knowing narrator becomes silence,the third person narrator accepts the function of all-knowing narrator.In drama text,the second text narrator could be regarded as a narrator which is out of the story,and it narrates features or minds of people.In most of drama text,the second text narrator becomes silence,and the characters accept the function of narrator as the third person narrator."}
